parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Cam Bearings, Cam Support Plates, and Oil Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear cam bearings, cam support plates, and oil pump can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially life-threatening situations.
The failure of the kickstand/jiffy stand can cause the motorcycle to fall over, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially injuring the rider or bystanders.
symptoms: the motorcycle is unstable when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cam Bearing Failure and Camshaft Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cam bearing and camshaft can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially resulting in engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The sudden stalling of the engine can cause the motorcycle to lose power and momentum, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when traveling at high speeds. This can lead to serious injury or even death.
symptoms: the motorcycle loses power and momentum

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear motorcycle bearings can cause the motorcycle to vibrate excessively, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: wobbling or shaking of the motorcycle
and potential seizure of the rear wheel.
